Timeline: How coronavirus got started The outbreak spanning the globe began in December, in Wuhan, China.
Americans' response to coronavirus in MarchThe novel coronavirus outbreak, which began in Wuhan, China, in December, has expanded to touch nearly every corner of the globe.
Jan. 11, 2020: China reports 1st novel coronavirus deathChinese state media reports the first death from novel coronavirus, a 61-year-old man who had visited the live animal market in Wuhan.
Fabrice Coffrini/AFP via Getty ImagesFeb. 11, 2020: Novel coronavirus renamed COVID-19The WHO announces that novel coronavirus' formal new name is COVID-19.
March 17, 2020: Coronavirus now present in all 50 statesWest Virginia reports its first COVID-19 case, meaning the disease is present in all 50 states.